.TH "xas_split_alloc" 9 "xas_split_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xas_split_alloc \- Allocate memory for splitting an entry.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xas_split_alloc
.BI "(struct xa_state *xas "  ","
.BI "void *entry "  ","
.BI "unsigned int order "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xas" 12
XArray operation state.
.IP "entry" 12
New entry which will be stored in the array.
.IP "order" 12
Current entry order.
.IP "gfp" 12
Memory allocation flags.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should be called before calling \fBxas_split\fP.
If necessary, it will allocate new nodes (and fill them with \fIentry\fP)
to prepare for the upcoming split of an entry of \fIorder\fP size into
entries of the order stored in the \fIxas\fP.
.SH "CONTEXT"
May sleep if \fIgfp\fP flags permit.
